1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:42,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:52,217
Murder?

3
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:56,723
His breath smelled like almonds,
and his lips had turned blue.

4
00:00:57,098 --> 00:01:02,520
They also found a note on the table,
so they ruled it self-inflicted.

5
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:08,234
It's giving me headache,
but I have to do it.

6
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:11,255
How is that connected to our case?

7
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:14,491
Is there something going on
between you and Loki?

8
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:19,388
One seat apart!

9
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:20,705
What could've happened?

10
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:25,001
It means a lot of people
reported the account.

11
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:28,213
Just appeal and wait for 30 days.

12
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:30,149
You haven't violated anything.

13
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:35,762
You look like a dumb chihuahua
with no talents and art of detection.

14
00:01:40,850 --> 00:01:41,850
I'm here!

15
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:44,020
Finally! Loki! You're here!

16
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:48,649
Are you okay?

17
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:53,613
Yeah, of course.

18
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:04,582
Let's go? Rehearsals are about to start.

19
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:10,338
You'll actually see me on stage later.

20
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:13,067
Oh, my God! I'm so excited!

21
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:16,219
And here, you'll see our TDR.

22
00:02:16,761 --> 00:02:20,324
Oh, my God. Where are my org mates?

23
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:22,851
- Oh, they're already here.
- Wait.

24
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:33,611
Are you ready?

25
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,824
♪ Shadows ♪

26
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:40,827
♪ in the dark are crawling. ♪

27
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:45,558
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

28
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:49,127
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

29
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:53,649
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

30
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:56,819
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

31
00:02:56,843 --> 00:02:59,780
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

32
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:04,309
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪

33
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,812
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

34
00:03:09,063 --> 00:03:11,441
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

35
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:16,196
♪ For this world ♪

36
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,466
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

37
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:21,951
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

38
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:25,079
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

39
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:29,918
♪ For this world ♪

40
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:33,147
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

41
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:38,009
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

42
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:40,929
Oh, my God! Jamie!

43
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:44,224
- Hi, guys!
- Jamie is here!

44
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:47,769
So, guys, these are my friends
who want to see our rehearsals.

45
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,814
This is Loki and that's Lorelei.

46
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,942
They are here to observe.

47
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:57,904
Don't worry, they won't interrupt
during rehearsals.

48
00:03:58,112 --> 00:03:59,673
Oh, friends, huh?

49
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:03,076
You didn't tell us you were acquainted
with the Q.E.D. members.

50
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,118
Yeah.

51
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:07,705
So, what? Should we assume
they're here to investigate?

52
00:04:08,473 --> 00:04:09,474
No.

53
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:15,171
I'm here to write an article
for the Clarion about the plays,

54
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,631
so I just asked Loki to come with me.

55
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:18,968
I see.

56
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:24,549
Oh, sorry, I didn't get to thank you
and introduce myself in person, but

57
00:04:24,574 --> 00:04:28,036
I'm Stein Alberts,
and I'm pleased to meet the two of you.

58
00:04:28,930 --> 00:04:32,230
Stein Alberts. Third year, BS Math.

59
00:04:32,834 --> 00:04:34,210
Actually, he's really good.

60
00:04:34,737 --> 00:04:36,823
They say he's really smart,

61
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:39,487
so not many can relate to him.

62
00:04:40,712 --> 00:04:43,298
Pleased to meet you too. You're welcome.

63
00:04:43,817 --> 00:04:46,069
You're a member of the Repertory Club too?

64
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:50,748
Oh, yeah. If you need help,
especially with numbers, I can help.

65
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:53,668
It's the least I can do
to repay you for saving me.

66
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:55,813
Come on, guys! Enough gossip!

67
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:57,189
Come on! Let's rehearse!

68
00:04:57,213 --> 00:04:58,464
Let's go! Let's go!

69
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:00,466
Exciting!

70
00:05:03,594 --> 00:05:04,595
So…

71
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:11,728
What's a math prodigy like Stein
doing in the Repertory Club?

72
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:15,106
Yeah. I'm also wondering.

73
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:19,944
Anyway, observe their positions on stage.

74
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:22,488
Okay.

75
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:24,798
Okay, guys.
This is what we've been waiting for. Okay?

76
00:05:24,823 --> 00:05:25,801
Let's rehearse.

77
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,845
Act One, we're starting. Okay, go!

78
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:30,997
- Break a leg!
- Break a leg, guys!

79
00:05:31,264 --> 00:05:35,352
For it seems I am being watched by him.

80
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:43,092
His deep, sorrowful eyes unsettle me.

81
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:46,888
When he stares at me.

82
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:50,475
I get scared.

83
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:54,687
When he speaks to me

84
00:05:56,314 --> 00:06:01,569
he has a voice that tells me things
that are truly strange

85
00:06:05,698 --> 00:06:07,283
that are beyond understanding,

86
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,537
truly peculiar.

87
00:06:12,663 --> 00:06:15,458
Find a way to keep him from coming here.

88
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:19,087
It's a pleasant breeze, isn't it?

89
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:22,090
Once it catches a cold,

90
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:26,636
it clings on until summer comes.

91
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:31,724
Aren't you worried you might get cold?

92
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,084
Everyone, listen up!

93
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:42,878
Number one reminder to all of you,
don't turn to your backs.

94
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,155
The audience is here,
they won't see your facial expressions.

95
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:48,550
- Okay?
- Einstein is not leaving his spot

96
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:50,174
- in front of stage.
- Okay, let's start.

97
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:53,347
- Just Stein.
- Everyone on the side, move a little...

98
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:56,874
But it looks like he's fixing the blocking.

99
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,918
Could he be the floor director?

100
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:00,878
- You there, on the side...
- In fairness,

101
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:04,549
he's already good at math,
and also at the arts.

102
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,485
- Talented.
- Noted.

103
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,678
What's the point of being talented
if you're a creep?

104
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,138
Action!

105
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:11,347
Come on.

106
00:07:11,891 --> 00:07:13,684
He's just a suspect for now, right?

107
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:15,142
Whatever.

108
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:17,603
What about the other guy?

109
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:19,939
I don't know what his role is,

110
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,917
- but he's been peeking...
- Wesley, line.

111
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:23,192
From the side of the stage.

112
00:07:23,651 --> 00:07:25,194
- You see him?
- Lines, please.

113
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:27,196
I don't know either.

114
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,134
- Maybe he's in props?
- Okay, let's go through the script.

115
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:32,052
- Or wardrobe?
- I've already given you your lines.

116
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:33,470
Maybe he's the stage manager?

117
00:07:33,494 --> 00:07:35,889
- You have the time to memorize.
- I'm not sure.

118
00:07:35,913 --> 00:07:41,043
I mean, they probably still have
a tech team that's not onstage yet.

119
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:42,503
Okay?

120
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:45,047
- We're clear. Okay.
- Okay, here's what we'll do…

121
00:07:45,923 --> 00:07:49,677
During their break,
let's split up and interview the members.

122
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:50,738
I'll take Stein.

123
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:52,072
Alright, from the top.

124
00:07:52,096 --> 00:07:54,724
- Okay, got it.
- Everyone, no extra movements, please.

125
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:00,706
Ibarra, you have to move

126
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:01,981
Maria Clara.

127
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,042
So this is confirmed. That's all.

128
00:08:04,066 --> 00:08:06,545
The blocking's good,
I'll just run it again with them.

129
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:07,963
- Yup.
- Thank you.

130
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:09,071
Excuse me.

131
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:11,741
Hi, I'm Lorelei.

132
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,202
I'm from the Q.E.D. Club.

133
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:19,415
Can I interview you for the article
I'm writing for the Clarion?

134
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:22,919
- You're Jamie's friend?
- Yes.

135
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:27,006
Friend of Jamie. Okay.

136
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:28,716
Will this take long?

137
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,094
We still have a lot
we haven't rehearsed yet.

138
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:35,056
Sorry. This will be quick.

139
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:37,350
Anyway

140
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,896
what's your name
and what's your role in the play?

141
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:45,691
Wesley Nuñez, stage manager.

142
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:01,499
What's a math major
like yourself doing here?

143
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,795
Shouldn't you be solving
complex mathematical equations?

144
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:08,214
Not making plays.

145
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:10,505
I'm this play's director.

146
00:09:11,427 --> 00:09:14,321
I'm the one who assigns the actors
their blocking,

147
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:18,933
where to enter, stand, or exit the stage.

148
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:21,143
I see.

149
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,229
So you're always in front of the stage,

150
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:26,899
watching the production
from the audience's point of view.

151
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:28,776
Right?

152
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:33,030
Are you interrogating me right now?

153
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:37,159
Or am I a suspect to you now?

154
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,203
I'm just asking questions.

155
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:43,249
You're way too serious.

156
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:48,045
Can you tell me
what a stage manager usually does?

157
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:51,299
Didn't Jamie brief you?

158
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:55,428
Oh, come on. Okay.

159
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:57,030
As the stage manager,

160
00:09:57,054 --> 00:10:00,349
I make sure everyone here is present.

161
00:10:00,516 --> 00:10:01,785
Actors and crew.

162
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:04,770
Before rehearsals
and before the play starts.

163
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:07,291
I'm also in charge of cueing the actors.

164
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:10,109
When it's their turn,
I send them into the scene.

165
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:13,279
Okay? I basically manage everything here.

166
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:16,949
Imagine if I weren't here,
this would all be chaos.

167
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:21,829
So, where are you usually positioned?

168
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:25,041
Well, I'm mostly at the side of the stage.

169
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:32,149
I watch the scene
to see if I have notes for the actors.

170
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:35,760
If they can enter and exit the stage.

171
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:39,347
To answer your question, yes.

172
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:45,561
As director, it's my job to ensure the
audience gets a high-quality experience.

173
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,230
That's why I'm sitting here
in the front row.

174
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:55,905
And just because I'm good at math
doesn't mean I can't be creative.

175
00:10:57,406 --> 00:10:58,449
Right?

176
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:12,963
Sorry. What's going on up in the balcony?

177
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:16,759
Oh, that's Alvin. He's the sound guy.

178
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:18,195
Okay. I see.

179
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,304
Are we good? I have to go.

180
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:21,514
Oh, yes! Yes!

181
00:11:21,555 --> 00:11:23,641
I need to study our next scene.

182
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:25,827
Sure. Thank you for your time.

183
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:28,562
Okay. Alright. Thank you!

184
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:34,652
Okay, guys!
Let's focus on Act Two, alright?

185
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:36,237
Hey.

186
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,241
There.

187
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:42,451
There.

188
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:47,498
There.

189
00:11:51,293 --> 00:11:52,336
Excuse me.

190
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:55,107
Is there anything I can help you with?

191
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:57,651
Hi, are you Alvin?

192
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:00,302
Yes, I'm Alvin. Alvin Mendoza.

193
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:02,638
Why? Do you need something from me?

194
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:05,641
We just wanted to ask
if you've been here since last week.

195
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,519
In this exact same spot, I mean.

196
00:12:08,602 --> 00:12:11,897
What he means is,
what's your assignment in the play?

197
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,775
Are you always stationed here?

198
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,778
Oh, yeah. I'm usually stationed here.

199
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:20,239
I'm assigned to the sound system.

200
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,617
Wait, who are you?

201
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:26,746
Hey, if someone stole
something backstage, it wasn't me!

202
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:29,850
I go straight here during rehearsals,

203
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,274
I don't pass through there anymore.

204
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:34,253
I only go down when it's company call.

205
00:12:34,378 --> 00:12:37,465
Don't worry, nothing was stolen.

206
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:40,509
Loki!

207
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:46,408
Thanks, Alvin. Sorry about him.

208
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:49,602
He's in a hurry. He's got a deadline.

209
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:51,729
- I'll go ahead.
- Take care.

210
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:54,607
Loki, wait!

211
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:59,153
Hey! You left so fast!

212
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:04,033
You didn't even thank Alvin
after we talked to him.

213
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:06,619
Where's the other guy on our list?

214
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:07,870
Huh?

215
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:11,081
The last guy from our list.

216
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,334
Are you guys okay?

217
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:15,878
Are you new members of the club?

218
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:17,963
What's your role in the play?

219
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:20,424
Do we look like idiots to you...

220
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:23,093
Oh, no! We're Jamie's friends.

221
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:26,239
- We're here to observe the rehearsal.
- Okay.

222
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:28,891
Raymond! Hurry up! We're hungry!

223
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:31,661
Sorry, the line at the convenience store
was so long.

224
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:32,603
Why don't you go instead?

225
00:13:32,686 --> 00:13:34,188
We're starving here!

226
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:38,776
Do you always go out
to buy snacks for other members?

227
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:43,697
Yeah, that's my duty
as assistant production manager.

228
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,452
Eat first.

229
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:51,956
Thank you.

230
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:54,082
Welcome.

231
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:57,669
Okay.

232
00:13:58,379 --> 00:13:59,380
Okay.

233
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:05,052
So now that we've met our four suspects,
who do you think is our mystery guy?

234
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:43,632
What happened?

235
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,763
Leave us for now
for a sacred confession.

236
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:51,807
But, Father...

237
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,434
Hurry.

238
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:08,073
How are you feeling, Maria Clara?

239
00:15:09,658 --> 00:15:11,535
Are you feeling better now?

240
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:17,041
Maria Clara, it's me, Father Salvi.

241
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:22,755
Maria Clara, listen to
me. God will help you.

242
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:24,965
I'll help you, okay?

243
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:27,176
You'll get better from your illness.

244
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:35,726
Hey!

245
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:37,770
Who do you think it is?

246
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:43,025
Wesley Nuñez.

247
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,362
You're indeed learning from me.

248
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:49,114
We have the same culprit in mind.

249
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:51,867
So, what do we do now?

250
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:55,829
That's it! Good job, everyone!

251
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,433
Good job!

252
00:15:58,457 --> 00:16:00,352
- Bye, guys!
- Bye!

253
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,938
- Bye-bye!
- Bye!

254
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,105
Take care. We'll go ahead now.

255
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,756
Good luck! Bye!

256
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,424
I love you!

257
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:13,097
We have to go too.

258
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:15,909
We'll just wait for you
at the Q.E.D. club room.

259
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:16,933
Okay.

260
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,936
Okay, Loki. See you later!

261
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:48,507
Shocks.

262
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:51,093
Jamie! Are you okay?

263
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,805
Aren't you going home yet, Wes?

264
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:58,151
- I'm still fixing the props here on stage.
- Why are you still here?

265
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:02,771
My head really hurts.

266
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:08,444
You look dizzy. Rest for a while.

267
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,760
Maybe I'm just sleep-deprived,
that's why I feel dizzy.

268
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:17,161
Lie down for a bit.

269
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:22,166
I won't stay up late for now, so...

270
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:27,628
Jamie?

271
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:29,505
Jamie!

272
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:34,845
Is anyone there?

273
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:38,640
Help! Someone!

274
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:48,502
I have a confession.

275
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:52,131
I love you, Jamie.

276
00:18:58,262 --> 00:18:59,680
Get your hands off her!

277
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,892
- Lorelei! Lorelei!
- You bastard!

278
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:05,078
- Lorelei.
- Pervert!

279
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:07,914
- Lorelei, enough. Lorelei.
- Asshole!

280
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:09,749
- Lorelei.
- Let go of me, Loki!

281
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:11,525
Lorelei! Stop!

282
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:13,878
Let go of me!

283
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:15,487
Lorelei, stop, stop, stop.

284
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:19,366
Wait. Why are you still here?

285
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:22,202
Nothing happened here.

286
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:24,413
Don't try to deny it!

287
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,416
We got everything you planned to do
on camera!

288
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:34,590
Your minds are so dirty!

289
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:37,426
I'm sure your video angle is wrong.

290
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:39,178
She fainted, okay?

291
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:41,346
I was just helping her!

292
00:19:41,889 --> 00:19:43,348
I was gonna take her to the clinic.

293
00:19:43,807 --> 00:19:48,437
But this girl, she shoved me,
and you even beat me up!

294
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:51,522
Liar.

295
00:19:52,232 --> 00:19:53,775
Really, Wes?

296
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:57,195
Jamie?

297
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:01,283
You're okay?

298
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:04,286
You're okay?

299
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,247
Are you okay? I thought...

300
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:10,375
You didn't even notice I was acting?

301
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:14,755
Was my acting really that convincing, Wes?

302
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:16,548
Wait.

303
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:18,800
How...

304
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,141
Wait.

305
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:31,230
One of these boys
is probably your mysterious chat mate.

306
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:36,401
Our plan now is for Lorelei and me
to speak with the suspects.

307
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:40,155
We'll find out what they usually do
during rehearsals.

308
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:43,635
And once we have a strong suspicion
of who it is,

309
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:47,180
we need to lure our prey
out of his hiding hole

310
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:48,580
to get evidence.

311
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:52,709
Wait, Loki,
are you really sure about your plan?

312
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:55,545
Isn't that too dangerous for Jamie?

313
00:20:56,213 --> 00:21:00,384
She's with us, so don't worry.
It's not like before.

314
00:21:01,301 --> 00:21:03,262
No surprises are going to happen.

315
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:08,058
And Jamie is fully aware of this plan
to avoid any misunderstanding.

316
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:14,106
Besides, this plan won't push through
if we don't have Jamie's full consent.

317
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:17,985
Are you okay with this?

318
00:21:18,652 --> 00:21:20,713
That's actually a cool idea.

319
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:25,200
If you think it'll work,
I'm fine with it as long as we catch him.

320
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:29,555
And I can defend
myself if it comes to that.

321
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:33,292
I know basic self-defense. Yeah.

322
00:21:34,084 --> 00:21:38,630
Okay, so now that we've met
our four suspects,

323
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:40,590
who do you think is our mystery guy?

324
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:44,511
Wesley Nuñez.

325
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:47,806
We have the same culprit in mind.

326
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:49,850
Really? Who?

327
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:51,935
It's Wesley Nuñez.

328
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:55,856
Wes? How exactly is he involved?

329
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:02,380
In all the photos Jamie sent,

330
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:05,490
the subject's always turned away
or from the side.

331
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:07,593
This means they were captured

332
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:11,496
while the perpetrator was either behind
or beside the target.

333
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:17,127
- So, Stan can't do that.
- Stein.

334
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:21,298
Stein, because he's always at the front.

335
00:22:22,049 --> 00:22:24,277
If he really is Mister Y,

336
00:22:24,301 --> 00:22:28,263
Wes would've sent her nothing
but front shots of Jamie.

337
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:31,743
Alvin, the sound guy, can't do that either.

338
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:36,873
Because his position is too far away
to get a close shot of Jamie.

339
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:39,751
And he said he doesn't go backstage,

340
00:22:39,775 --> 00:22:42,819
which automatically eliminated him
from the list.

341
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:50,094
The assistant production manager
is out of the question too

342
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:53,163
since he's always gone to get food
when rehearsals start.

343
00:22:53,705 --> 00:22:54,849
On top of that,

344
00:22:54,873 --> 00:22:58,895
he arranges the snacks he bought
in the audience area instead of backstage.

345
00:22:58,919 --> 00:23:02,065
The only one left on the list is Wesley.

346
00:23:02,089 --> 00:23:05,526
Wesley is the most likely one
sending you the photos in chat

347
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:09,554
because he's in the right position
and angle to take them.

348
00:23:13,683 --> 00:23:15,453
Being the stage manager,

349
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:20,124
it wouldn't look suspicious for Wesley to
go to the left or right wing of the stage

350
00:23:20,148 --> 00:23:22,752
and secretly take pictures of Jamie

351
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:25,445
while she's acting
in the center of the stage.

352
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:32,327
Now is the time
to turn our plans into actions.

353
00:23:32,744 --> 00:23:34,496
We're going to need your help.

354
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:37,582
Okay! What do I do?

355
00:23:39,709 --> 00:23:41,795
This is where your acting skills
would come in.

356
00:23:42,921 --> 00:23:46,091
We need you to lure him out
so we can secure an evidence.

357
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,010
Oh, my God! Exciting! Game!

358
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:54,909
If you suddenly feel
like you can't handle it,

359
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:56,518
just let us know, okay?

360
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,812
We're just right here.

361
00:23:59,187 --> 00:24:01,523
Don't worry, I can do it!

362
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:06,528
We have to wait for the right moment
to get solid evidence.

363
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:09,614
And yet, viola!

364
00:24:10,907 --> 00:24:12,159
You gave it to us.

365
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:15,787
With her testimony and video evidence,

366
00:24:16,538 --> 00:24:20,333
you're getting a one-way ticket
to the Office of Student Affairs.

367
00:24:20,876 --> 00:24:23,503
And we're also here to stand as witnesses.

368
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:26,923
I hope you learned something
from your actors.

369
00:24:27,757 --> 00:24:30,427
You might need to pull a convincing act

370
00:24:30,927 --> 00:24:34,639
to slither your way out of here,
stage manager.

371
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:37,725
No.

372
00:24:38,393 --> 00:24:39,436
That's not true.

373
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:43,606
No!

374
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:54,409
Are you okay?

375
00:24:55,118 --> 00:24:57,704
Yes. I'm very much okay. Thank you!

376
00:24:57,954 --> 00:24:59,557
He's either getting expelled,

377
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:03,960
or he'll just drop out from the shame
before that even happens.

378
00:25:04,252 --> 00:25:06,505
Find a new stage manager now.

379
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:13,386
Thank you for allowing yourself
to be a bait on this plan.

380
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:17,224
No problem! I know you won't let me down.

381
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:21,770
And, actually, seeing you in action,

382
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,731
you impressed me even more, Loki.

383
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:33,657
Our club's door is always open
if you ever need our help.

384
00:25:35,575 --> 00:25:37,285
Thank you for everything.

385
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:17,510
One of the biggest fears many women carry

386
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:19,845
is the fear of being powerless.

387
00:26:19,869 --> 00:26:23,498
A fear rooted
in a long history of inequality.

388
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:30,314
Like in Jose Rizal's novel,
Noli Me Tangere,

389
00:26:30,338 --> 00:26:35,302
Maria Clara is powerless at the hands
of those she believed were allies of God.

390
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:40,908
This illustrates
that even in literature and history,

391
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:45,562
women in colonial Philippine society,
were among the most vulnerable.

392
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:50,626
But today, women are finding ways

393
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:53,528
to claim their rights
and resist that vulnerability.

394
00:26:55,905 --> 00:26:59,594
Recently, we stopped another case
from turning into a tragedy.

395
00:26:59,618 --> 00:27:02,597
Our client, who asked to stay anonymous,

396
00:27:02,621 --> 00:27:04,765
reached out to us
because she wanted to find out

397
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:08,668
who was stalking her
and secretly taking photos of her.

398
00:27:11,713 --> 00:27:12,815
Stop it!

399
00:27:12,839 --> 00:27:15,508
She was frightened and felt helpless.

400
00:27:18,345 --> 00:27:22,033
But in the end,
that fear made her stronger.

401
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:27,437
She turned her vulnerability into strength
and helped us catch the culprit.

402
00:27:29,522 --> 00:27:30,565
No!

403
00:27:33,068 --> 00:27:35,612
I admire Jamie's courage,

404
00:27:36,404 --> 00:27:39,407
but I can't read what's in her mind.

405
00:27:40,033 --> 00:27:42,994
It feels like she's hiding more.

406
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:50,710
What's going on in your head, woman?

407
00:27:52,879 --> 00:27:55,256
Shoot! Oh, shoot!

408
00:27:56,257 --> 00:27:57,509
Come on, Lori.

409
00:27:58,843 --> 00:28:01,554
Her story reminds us
of something important.

410
00:28:01,846 --> 00:28:04,158
Fear does not always make us weak.

411
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:07,602
Sometimes,
women become stronger and braver

412
00:28:07,644 --> 00:28:10,313
when another woman stands beside them.

413
00:28:18,321 --> 00:28:20,675
Support like this can be the very force

414
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:23,743
that pushes women
to rise and stay strong.

415
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:01,239
Come in!

416
00:29:04,325 --> 00:29:06,745
Hi, guys! Missed me?

417
00:29:07,537 --> 00:29:11,082
Jamie! Hi. What's up?

418
00:29:11,499 --> 00:29:13,543
Do you have a concern you want to raise?

419
00:29:14,627 --> 00:29:17,255
Nothing. It's just.

420
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:22,218
I want to join this club!

421
00:29:22,969 --> 00:29:24,387
Wait, what?

422
00:29:24,679 --> 00:29:27,640
I want to be part of this Q.E.D. Club.

423
00:29:28,016 --> 00:29:30,185
You're still accepting members, right?

424
00:29:31,895 --> 00:29:32,937
Loki?

425
00:29:42,864 --> 00:29:44,199
- Yay!
- Once you're done,

426
00:29:44,741 --> 00:29:47,202
- send it to me for approval.
- Okay.

427
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:51,372
Jamie Santiago...

428
00:29:51,706 --> 00:29:53,208
Done. Okay.

429
00:29:53,625 --> 00:29:58,105
I'll tell Clark Repertory
I can't join the play for now

430
00:29:58,129 --> 00:30:01,049
because I want to focus on Q.E.D Club.

431
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:04,886
I'm so happy! Thank you, Loki!

432
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:07,931
Bye, Lori!

433
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:14,646
You know, you've been acting weird
ever since you met Jamie.

434
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:17,291
First, you keep spacing out,

435
00:30:17,315 --> 00:30:20,610
and you just freeze in your seat
like some kind of statue.

436
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:25,824
Second, you accepted her application
to the club right away.

437
00:30:26,241 --> 00:30:30,161
But with Rosetta's,
you turned it down right away.

438
00:30:30,829 --> 00:30:33,224
And now you can't even look at her.

439
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:36,751
So tell me, is there something going on
between you two?

440
00:30:38,586 --> 00:30:41,464
If I had known that would be
my last photo with Rhea.

441
00:30:42,298 --> 00:30:45,093
I would have turned to the camera
and forced a smile.

442
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:48,179
Huh? What are you talking about?

443
00:30:53,059 --> 00:30:54,936
Jamie has a retentive memory.

444
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:58,523
Her acting skills are also commendable.

445
00:30:59,148 --> 00:31:04,237
Bottomline, she has assets
that may come in handy.

446
00:31:04,571 --> 00:31:06,739
I hope you understand my decision.

447
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:13,848
Wait, where are you going?

448
00:31:13,872 --> 00:31:15,039
Coffee.

449
00:31:39,981 --> 00:31:41,316
Loki?

450
00:31:45,361 --> 00:31:47,989
Loki! This is important.

451
00:31:55,496 --> 00:31:56,496
Hi.

452
00:31:56,706 --> 00:31:58,666
Why are you waking me up on a Saturday?

453
00:32:00,376 --> 00:32:01,878
At 2 in the morning!

454
00:32:03,713 --> 00:32:05,089
Loki, I.

455
00:32:05,798 --> 00:32:07,258
I need your help.

456
00:32:10,136 --> 00:32:12,656
We don't accept requests on weekends.

457
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,240
You can tell me your problem on Monday.

458
00:32:14,557 --> 00:32:17,810
Please? This is a personal request.

459
00:32:17,936 --> 00:32:19,312
So please hear me out.

460
00:32:20,229 --> 00:32:22,690
Okay. I'm listening.

461
00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:26,110
But that doesn't mean I'll help you.

462
00:32:27,236 --> 00:32:28,905
It still depends on your request.

463
00:32:35,411 --> 00:32:37,789
Hi, Lori! How are you?

464
00:32:38,665 --> 00:32:41,042
It's been a while since we last talked.

465
00:32:41,918 --> 00:32:44,587
Oh, right. I'll go there tomorrow.

466
00:32:44,921 --> 00:32:48,466
Are you free? Come on, let's have coffee!

467
00:32:49,092 --> 00:32:51,344
Okay. So why do you need my help?

468
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:55,473
You can't handle a conversation
with a dear friend on your own?

469
00:32:55,682 --> 00:32:58,476
Because I can't turn down his invitation!

470
00:32:59,435 --> 00:33:01,771
He's asking me out and

471
00:33:02,397 --> 00:33:06,401
if I agree to meet him
and he finds out I'm single,

472
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:11,739
he might transfer to Clark U
just to follow and court me.

473
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:15,076
So I thought, so I can reject him,

474
00:33:15,702 --> 00:33:18,121
maybe I can tell him
that I have a boyfriend.

475
00:33:18,579 --> 00:33:20,498
Okay, then. Bring your boyfriend.

476
00:33:22,333 --> 00:33:23,333
Wait...

477
00:33:26,295 --> 00:33:27,588
That's the thing.

478
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:31,259
I've never been in a relationship before.

479
00:33:31,634 --> 00:33:36,848
And that's the help
I was going to ask from you.

480
00:33:40,101 --> 00:33:41,101
Loki...

481
00:33:41,728 --> 00:33:43,646
Loki, I want you to be my boyfriend.

482
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:50,611
Loki! I'm being serious!

483
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:52,613
I'm not kidding!

484
00:33:54,532 --> 00:33:56,117
Are you trying to play a trick on me?

485
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:59,096
You're way too late
for an April Fools' Day prank.

486
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:01,039
Don't flatter yourself, Loki!

487
00:34:01,372 --> 00:34:04,333
I just need you to pretend
to be my boyfriend,

488
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:05,918
for today!

489
00:34:06,544 --> 00:34:08,504
Just for one or two hours!

490
00:34:09,255 --> 00:34:10,423
Please?

491
00:35:02,558 --> 00:35:03,558
Wow.

492
00:35:04,685 --> 00:35:06,687
You can actually dress well.

493
00:35:07,939 --> 00:35:08,940
You look

494
00:35:09,649 --> 00:35:10,691
nice.

495
00:35:13,027 --> 00:35:16,924
Like you, I've never been
in a relationship before

496
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:21,410
so I don't know
how to be a believable boyfriend.

497
00:35:22,537 --> 00:35:23,579
Really?

498
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:26,457
But, don't worry.

499
00:35:26,916 --> 00:35:30,795
I've done my research
on how a proper date is done.

500
00:35:31,516 --> 00:35:33,185
So as far as acting goes,

501
00:35:34,068 --> 00:35:35,236
you can count on me.

502
00:35:35,919 --> 00:35:37,003
Really?

503
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:39,929
I think I may be of assistance to you.

504
00:35:41,276 --> 00:35:42,402
Shall we go?

505
00:36:04,453 --> 00:36:05,764
After you.

506
00:36:05,788 --> 00:36:06,831
Sorry.

507
00:36:07,957 --> 00:36:08,957
After you.

508
00:36:09,584 --> 00:36:10,584
You first.

509
00:36:10,918 --> 00:36:11,919
Go ahead.

510
00:36:12,712 --> 00:36:14,172
Go ahead. After you.

511
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:22,013
Wow!

512
00:36:22,722 --> 00:36:25,558
My kids look so good!

513
00:36:25,641 --> 00:36:26,934
So where's your date?

514
00:36:26,976 --> 00:36:29,656
- Oh, we're not going on a date, Tita!
- Just in a café at the mall.

515
00:36:29,687 --> 00:36:33,316
The sun's blazing,
and you're still talking in unison. Okay.

516
00:36:33,983 --> 00:36:35,752
We're really not going on a date, Tita.

517
00:36:35,776 --> 00:36:38,321
We just have a school activity to attend.

518
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:41,574
Okay, okay, okay! If you say so.

519
00:36:41,908 --> 00:36:46,829
Take care, okay?
Loki, look after my niece, she might fall.

520
00:36:50,374 --> 00:36:52,084
- Take care!
- Alright.

521
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:03,387
Sorry.

522
00:37:03,971 --> 00:37:06,390
Let's see. What do couples do?

523
00:37:07,516 --> 00:37:08,809
Put your arm around me.

524
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:12,897
- Like this?
- Not like that! Not like that!

525
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:20,029
- Don't couples usually hold hands?
- What are you doing?

526
00:37:20,988 --> 00:37:23,866
Forget it. You don't know how.

527
00:37:46,889 --> 00:37:47,890
Thank you!

528
00:37:58,484 --> 00:38:00,486
Thanks a lot, I guess.

529
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:05,366
So, is this friend of yours dear to you?

530
00:38:05,950 --> 00:38:08,202
Yes. He's a childhood friend.

531
00:38:10,204 --> 00:38:11,204
I see.

532
00:38:11,747 --> 00:38:13,708
You seem well-dressed
for a simple catch up.

533
00:38:14,709 --> 00:38:16,909
Is there something going on
between you and your friend?

534
00:38:17,003 --> 00:38:18,587
Huh? Nothing!

535
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:22,633
And I've always dressed like this.

536
00:38:23,884 --> 00:38:27,972
Actually, I just noticed, you look like
you're heading to a job interview.

537
00:38:28,014 --> 00:38:29,682
- Huh?
- Not on a date.

538
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:34,270
You're only saying that now
that we're here?

539
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,106
I'll order some drinks.

540
00:38:37,523 --> 00:38:39,167
- What do you want to order?
- He's here!

541
00:38:39,191 --> 00:38:40,752
- He's here!
- Coffee's good.

542
00:38:40,776 --> 00:38:42,087
Hi, Draco!

543
00:38:42,111 --> 00:38:44,423
- Hi. How are you? Hi.
- Hi! Hi, Draco!

544
00:38:44,447 --> 00:38:45,549
- How are you?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

545
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:47,009
- Hi. How are you?
- How are you, guys?

546
00:38:47,033 --> 00:38:48,802
I thought you weren't coming.

547
00:38:48,826 --> 00:38:50,178
Was it super traffic?

548
00:38:50,202 --> 00:38:51,329
Yeah, totally!

549
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:56,917
- Anyway, let's order. My treat!
- Wow!

550
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:59,813
- Okay, I'll have black tea. You?
- Me too!

551
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:00,897
- Black, of course.
- Okay.

552
00:39:00,921 --> 00:39:03,174
That makes four of us then. Anything else?

553
00:39:03,507 --> 00:39:05,402
Try their honey-glazed donuts.

554
00:39:05,426 --> 00:39:06,611
- They're so good, I promise!
- Okay.

555
00:39:06,635 --> 00:39:10,574
Sir, can we have four honey-glazed donuts
and four black teas?

556
00:39:10,598 --> 00:39:12,576
- Okay, ma'am.
- Thank you.

557
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:14,310
You know what happened...

558
00:39:14,727 --> 00:39:15,787
You're talking to a lot of people, huh?

559
00:39:15,811 --> 00:39:18,314
- We've been starving waiting for you.
- You took so long.

560
00:39:18,731 --> 00:39:20,792
My dad just picked me up.

561
00:39:20,816 --> 00:39:23,819
So, your childhood friend is not here yet?

562
00:39:24,695 --> 00:39:27,281
He's not here yet.
Maybe he got stuck in traffic.

563
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:31,327
I mean, the guy at the next table
said he got stuck in traffic.

564
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:33,746
Oh, okay.

565
00:39:34,789 --> 00:39:37,333
So, eavesdropping is your thing now, huh?

566
00:39:37,875 --> 00:39:39,335
Very funny, Loki.

567
00:39:40,044 --> 00:39:41,855
You probably left the house late.

568
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:43,798
- Gosh!
- Sorry.

569
00:39:43,881 --> 00:39:45,800
- Oh, my God.
- It's okay.

570
00:39:46,175 --> 00:39:47,361
Did you get wet?

571
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:48,653
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Let me handle it.

572
00:39:48,677 --> 00:39:50,930
- No, it's okay, sir.
- Sorry.

573
00:39:51,180 --> 00:39:53,349
- Let's just transfer.
- I'm so sorry!

574
00:39:53,933 --> 00:39:56,018
- Sorry.
- Sorry, sir.

575
00:39:57,311 --> 00:39:58,729
Thank you, sir.

576
00:40:00,689 --> 00:40:02,793
Guys, I'm just going to the CR.

577
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:04,276
- Okay.
- Yeah, sure.

578
00:40:05,277 --> 00:40:06,338
What happened?

579
00:40:06,362 --> 00:40:08,298
- I feel bad for him.
- I know!

580
00:40:08,322 --> 00:40:09,949
Is there no creamer here?

581
00:40:10,282 --> 00:40:13,202
Huh? What's the creamer for?

582
00:40:13,494 --> 00:40:15,222
You didn't even order coffee.

583
00:40:15,246 --> 00:40:17,331
Hey, you know he loves creamer.

584
00:40:17,706 --> 00:40:19,667
Alright, I'll go get the creamer.

585
00:40:43,149 --> 00:40:45,067
Sir, ma'am. Here's your order.

586
00:40:52,741 --> 00:40:54,452
- Thank you.
- Okay, ma'am.

587
00:40:59,415 --> 00:41:02,209
Do you think those three girls
like that guy?

588
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:03,710
Huh?

589
00:41:04,253 --> 00:41:05,504
What do you mean?

590
00:41:06,505 --> 00:41:10,009
They all stare at him with dreamy eyes
with the chance presents itself.

591
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:13,447
But the guy is completely clueless

592
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:15,764
about how his friends
really feel about him.

593
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:20,811
You know, you're kind of a Marites too.

594
00:41:21,645 --> 00:41:22,855
Marites?

595
00:41:23,772 --> 00:41:24,815
Who's that?

596
00:41:27,109 --> 00:41:29,695
So sorry to keep you waiting, Lori.

597
00:41:34,825 --> 00:41:35,868
Al.

598
00:41:38,454 --> 00:41:39,497
Hi.

599
00:41:50,561 --> 00:41:52,782
It's been a while
since the last time I saw you.

600
00:41:53,547 --> 00:41:56,174
Sorry I couldn't reply to your messages.

601
00:41:56,263 --> 00:41:58,098
I lost signal on my phone.

602
00:42:03,896 --> 00:42:05,648
Sorry, you are?

603
00:42:07,733 --> 00:42:08,733
Loki.

604
00:42:12,363 --> 00:42:15,866
This is Loki, my classmate.

605
00:42:16,659 --> 00:42:17,785
And

606
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:21,622
my boyfriend.

607
00:42:23,624 --> 00:42:25,334
Oh, hi!

608
00:42:25,918 --> 00:42:27,062
Pleased to meet you.

609
00:42:27,086 --> 00:42:28,355
I'm Alistair Ravena.

610
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:30,506
Lori's childhood best friend
and ex-classmate.

611
00:42:34,969 --> 00:42:36,053
Loki Mendez.

612
00:42:36,595 --> 00:42:38,264
Pleased to make your acquaintance.

613
00:42:38,973 --> 00:42:41,100
You're lucky you won Lori's heart.

614
00:42:43,477 --> 00:42:44,520
Do you mind?

615
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:48,065
Are you really Lori's boyfriend?

616
00:42:49,984 --> 00:42:51,193
Yes, I am.

617
00:42:52,403 --> 00:42:53,988
Do you have a problem with that?

618
00:42:58,742 --> 00:43:01,662
I'm glad you found a good man, Lori.

619
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:13,340
- Let's have a seat?
- Yeah.

620
00:43:27,813 --> 00:43:29,523
What made you visit, by the way?

621
00:43:30,190 --> 00:43:31,859
I'm free right now.

622
00:43:32,109 --> 00:43:34,862
So I decided to visit you.

623
00:43:35,487 --> 00:43:38,657
I hope I'm not interrupting your plans.

624
00:43:40,909 --> 00:43:44,163
Wait. Did my father send you?

625
00:43:44,580 --> 00:43:48,125
Don't worry. I wanted to come here.
No one told me to.

626
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:50,753
I came here to check on you.

627
00:43:51,253 --> 00:43:53,881
Do you still keep in touch
with our old classmates?

628
00:43:56,342 --> 00:43:57,676
Not yet.

629
00:43:58,177 --> 00:44:00,846
And, to be honest, Al.

630
00:44:01,513 --> 00:44:04,308
I'm not ready to reconnect with them yet.

631
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:08,145
- I think I might need more time.
- Of course.

632
00:44:08,771 --> 00:44:11,565
I just got worried,
you weren't replying to my messages.

633
00:44:11,774 --> 00:44:14,252
I was worried
something might've happened,

634
00:44:14,276 --> 00:44:16,570
or if you're doing okay
at your new school.

635
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:20,658
But I get it if you weren't ready
to talk to me yet.

636
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:23,308
Is it because of what happened to her
in her previous school?

637
00:44:25,454 --> 00:44:27,915
She hasn't told me anything about it, so.

638
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:30,459
I'm quite curious.

639
00:44:33,837 --> 00:44:35,631
It's not my story to tell.

640
00:44:36,715 --> 00:44:38,342
I understand perfectly.

641
00:44:40,135 --> 00:44:41,720
Let's change the topic, okay?

642
00:44:42,471 --> 00:44:44,431
We're here to catch up, right?

643
00:44:45,057 --> 00:44:46,809
Not reopen old wounds.

644
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:49,311
Yeah. Sorry.

645
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:53,273
I'll just go to the counter.
I can get you guys anything.

646
00:44:53,691 --> 00:44:55,234
Donuts? Cheesecake?

647
00:44:55,275 --> 00:44:56,443
- Donuts!
- Cheesecake!

648
00:44:59,071 --> 00:45:00,071
Okay.

649
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:09,289
He's far from what I've expected.

650
00:45:09,832 --> 00:45:11,709
I thought he was chasing after you?

651
00:45:13,460 --> 00:45:14,712
Doesn't seem like it.

652
00:45:16,839 --> 00:45:18,132
Remind me again.

653
00:45:19,466 --> 00:45:22,052
Why did you ask me
to pretend to be your boyfriend?

654
00:45:29,643 --> 00:45:31,079
- Because...
- Draco? Draco?

655
00:45:31,103 --> 00:45:32,747
- Draco!
- What's happening?

656
00:45:32,771 --> 00:45:34,499
- What happened?
- What's happening?

657
00:45:34,523 --> 00:45:36,150
Oh, no. What happened?

658
00:45:36,442 --> 00:45:38,193
- Adriana, wait! Hold on!
- Draco!

659
00:45:39,111 --> 00:45:40,380
- Draco!
- I don't know!

660
00:45:40,404 --> 00:45:42,799
He was eating donuts
and then he collapsed to the floor.

661
00:45:42,823 --> 00:45:44,050
Draco, get up!

662
00:45:44,074 --> 00:45:45,552
- Someone call an ambulance!
- What's happening?

663
00:45:45,576 --> 00:45:49,246
- Draco! Help!
- Draco.

664
00:45:49,538 --> 00:45:51,832
- Hold on!
- Call an ambulance.

665
00:45:52,875 --> 00:45:57,254
I hope you don't mind if my colleague
will also help me in this case.

666
00:45:58,088 --> 00:46:00,299
Judging by the smell of almond
from his mouth

667
00:46:01,425 --> 00:46:04,887
the victim is poisoned
with Potassium Cyanide.

668
00:46:05,971 --> 00:46:09,016
You three are the primary suspects.

669
00:46:09,183 --> 00:46:12,019
Unfortunately, that might take some time.

670
00:46:12,519 --> 00:46:15,522
I'm dying to know
where they found the traces of poison.

671
00:46:18,734 --> 00:46:21,945
That Loki, is a remarkable man.

672
00:46:23,405 --> 00:46:26,366
Not everyone that age
can solve a case like this.

673
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:28,911
Pawn to D5.

674
00:46:29,411 --> 00:46:30,871
Knight to C3.

675
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:37,795
What are you guys doing?
Why do you look so serious?
